main event: On 7th September 1953 at 2100/30 in Omaha, Nebraska, an unusual sighting of round-shaped, red-colored objects was observed by credible witnesses.
interesting points: The objects displayed erratic speed and course changes, disappearing at high speed in the last 39 seconds of observation.
No physical evidence was found, and a visual and radar search by the base and nearby air control warning equipment detected nothing.
The reported objects did not correspond with the release of any known balloons, and extreme high altitude was deemed unlikely.
The UFO report was the first removed by Project Blue Book.
The document is classified as UNCLASSIFIED, with the declassification scheduled after 12 years.
witnesses: sales engineer, ex-military fighter pilot, housewife, major in SAC, and aircraft performance engineer
